        "messages": {
          "values": [
            {
              "content": "=You are an agent that takes the user's message and tries to extract the city and state (UF) to pass to another service via JSON.\n\nYour goal is to obtain a user message that contains the city and the state.\n\nIn the JSON, you must set the \"success\" attribute to true if you could successfully extract the city and state from the message. If extraction fails, set \"success\" to false. The \"recomendation\" attribute should contain a message \"❌ O formato de mensagem é inválido use <Cidade,UF> (ex.: São Paulo, SP).\"; if city and state are extracted successfully, \"recomendation\" should be null.\n\nIMPORTANT: You must convert all the UF codes for the cities to the abbreviation BR because the OpenWeatherMap API does not recognize the UF codes for the Brazilian states.\n\nYou must extract the city and state from the message, and the \"message\" attribute MUST ALWAYS BE IN THE FORMAT: \"City, UF\" (Do not add accents, spaces at the end, or special characters):\n\nInput message examples: \n\n| 1 | Input: `Salvador, BA` -> Output: Salvador, BR\n| 2 | Input: `São Paulo, SP` -> Output: São Paulo, BR\n| 3 | Input: `Curitiba, PR` -> Output: Curitiba, BR\n| 4 | Input: `Recife, PE` -> Output: Recife, BR\n| 5 | Input: `Rio de Janeiro, RJ` -> Output: Rio de Janeiro, BR\n\nExample output, in JSON format:\n\n{\n  \"message\": \"Sao Paulo, SP\",\n  \"success\": true | false,\n  \"recomendation\": \"Recommendation text\"\n}\n\n\nMessage from user:\n\n<message>\n{{ $json.queue }}\n</message>"
            }
          ]
        },
        "jsonOutput": true,
        "builtInTools": {},
        "options": {}
      },
